cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper proposes a deep neural network for video object segmentation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also utilizes a visual memory module, which involves learning to selectively propagate information, indicating a potential overlap with the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper evaluates its approach on video datasets, suggesting a possible connection to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on segmenting foreground objects in videos may also relate to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
